##



We have completed the following key tasks for Chapter 4.x: Lepton Horizon Theory, ensuring a robust and machine-checkable framework for the field.

Conceptual and Terminological Updates
We have established a 

"Terminology Bridge" to formalize our language.

The metric previously called "Meaning," a narrative term, is now confirmed to be mathematically identical to "Valence," our new operational term.

We will use "Meaning" for phenomenological discussions and "Valence" for formal mathematics and empirical testing.

This bridge ensures that all prior results from earlier chapters, when expressed as "Meaning," remain valid within the new, more precise context of 

Positive Geometry and Topology.

Core Components & Validations
